{{Expand English|Zinc finger nuclease}}
'''锌指核酸酶'''（{{lang-en|Zinc-finger nucleases, ZFNs}}），是人工改造的[[限制酶|限制酶]]，通过融合[[锌指结构|锌指结构]]的结合DNA[[结构域|结构域]]和分解DNA结构域而成。可通过基因工程改造锌指结构域使锌指核酸酶针对复杂基因组里的特定DNA序列。借助内源DNA的修复机制，锌指核酸酶可以精确改变高等动物的基因组。類似的技術還有[[類轉錄活化因子核酸酶|類轉錄活化因子核酸酶]]。

== 结构域 ==
锌指核酸酶是一种特定于位点的核酸[[限制酶|限制内切酶]]

功能：设计在特定的位置来结合并分解DNA，含有两个蛋白质[[结构域|结构域]]。

第一个结构域是DNA结合结构域，其由真核[[转录因子|转录因子]]并包含锌指所构成；第二个结构域是核酸酶结构域，它由[[FokI|FokI]]限制酶构成，并负责DNA的催化分解。

=== 分解DNA结构域 ===

[[File:Repair_outcomes_of_a_genomic_double-strand_break_for_ZFN_cleavage.jpg|thumb]]

type IIs [[核酸内切酶|核酸内切酶]] [[FokI|FokI]] 的非特异分解域经常被用做 ZFNs 的分解域，<ref name="kim1996">{{cite journal| last=Kim| first=YG| author2=Cha, J.| author3=Chandrasegaran, S.| year=1996| title=Hybrid restriction enzymes: zinc finger fusions to Fok I cleavage domain| journal=Proc Natl Acad Sci USA| volume=93| issue=3| pages=1156–60| url=http://www.pnas.org/content/93/3/1156.abstract| doi=10.1073/pnas.93.3.1156| pmid=8577732| pmc=40048| bibcode=1996PNAS...93.1156K| access-date=2014-12-05| archive-date=2015-01-28| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150128081204/http://www.pnas.org/content/93/3/1156.abstract| dead-url=no}}</ref>   
这个分解域需要二聚化来分解DNA。<ref name="bitinaite1998">{{cite journal| last=Bitinaite| first=J.| coauthors=D. A. Wah, Aggarwal, A. K., Schildkraut, I.| year=1998| title=FokI dimerization is required for DNA cleavage| journal=Proc Natl Acad Sci USA| volume=95| issue=18| pages=10570–5| url=http://www.pnas.org/cgi/content/full/95/18/10570| doi=10.1073/pnas.95.18.10570| pmid=9724744| pmc=27935| bibcode=1998PNAS...9510570B| access-date=2014-12-05| archive-date=2005-04-24| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20050424122954/http://www.pnas.org/cgi/content/full/95/18/10570| dead-url=no}}</ref> 
因此一对ZFNs只能用于定位非回文的DNA位点。标准的ZFNs每个域的碳端都融合了分离域。为了让两个分离域二聚化并分解DNA,两个单独的ZFNs需要结合在不同的DNA链上并且他们的碳端相隔一定的距离。在锌指域和分解域之间最常用的链接序列要求每个结合位点的5'端分隔5到7个bp。<ref>{{cite journal |author=Cathomen T, Joung JK |title=Zinc-finger nucleases: the next generation emerges |journal=Mol. Ther. |volume=16 |issue=7 |pages=1200–7 |date=July 2008 |pmid=18545224 |doi=10.1038/mt.2008.114 |url=http://www.nature.com/mt/journal/v16/n7/abs/mt2008114a.html |access-date=2014-12-05 |archive-date=2015-02-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150209121803/http://www.nature.com/mt/journal/v16/n7/abs/mt2008114a.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

几个不同的[[蛋白质工程|蛋白质工程]]技术已经用来提高用于ZFNs核酸酶域的活性和特异性。[[直接进化|直接进化]]被用来产生FokI的多样性以增强被作者称为"Sharkey"的<ref name=Guo2010>{{cite journal | last=Guo | first=Jing | last2=Gaj | first2=Thomas | last3=Barbas | first3=Carlos F. | title=Directed Evolution of an Enhanced and Highly Efficient FokI Cleavage Domain for Zinc Finger Nucleases | journal=Journal of Molecular Biology | publisher=Elsevier BV | volume=400 | issue=1 | year=2010 | issn=0022-2836 | doi=10.1016/j.jmb.2010.04.060 | pages=96–107}}</ref> 分解活性。通过修改二聚化的接口以便只有目的异二聚体类型有活性，基于结构的设计也被用来提高FokI的分解特异性。<ref name=Szczepek2007>{{cite journal | last=Szczepek | first=Michal | last2=Brondani | first2=Vincent | last3=Büchel | first3=Janine | last4=Serrano | first4=Luis | last5=Segal | first5=David J | last6=Cathomen | first6=Toni | title=Structure-based redesign of the dimerization interface reduces the toxicity of zinc-finger nucleases | journal=Nature Biotechnology | publisher=Springer Nature | volume=25 | issue=7 | year=2007 | issn=1087-0156 | doi=10.1038/nbt1317 | pages=786–793}}</ref><ref name=Miller2007>{{cite journal | last=Miller | first=Jeffrey C | last2=Holmes | first2=Michael C | last3=Wang | first3=Jianbin | last4=Guschin | first4=Dmitry Y | last5=Lee | first5=Ya-Li | last6=Rupniewski | first6=Igor | last7=Beausejour | first7=Christian M | last8=Waite | first8=Adam J | last9=Wang | first9=Nathaniel S | last10=Kim | first10=Kenneth A | last11=Gregory | first11=Philip D | last12=Pabo | first12=Carl O | last13=Rebar | first13=Edward J | title=An improved zinc-finger nuclease architecture for highly specific genome editing | journal=Nature Biotechnology | publisher=Springer Nature | volume=25 | issue=7 | year=2007 | issn=1087-0156 | doi=10.1038/nbt1319 | pages=778–785}}</ref><ref name=Doyon2010>{{cite journal | last=Doyon | first=Yannick | last2=Vo | first2=Thuy D | last3=Mendel | first3=Matthew C | last4=Greenberg | first4=Shon G | last5=Wang | first5=Jianbin | last6=Xia | first6=Danny F | last7=Miller | first7=Jeffrey C | last8=Urnov | first8=Fyodor D | last9=Gregory | first9=Philip D | last10=Holmes | first10=Michael C | title=Enhancing zinc-finger-nuclease activity with improved obligate heterodimeric architectures | journal=Nature Methods | publisher=Springer Nature | volume=8 | issue=1 | date=2010-12-05 | issn=1548-7091 | doi=10.1038/nmeth.1539 | pages=74–79}}</ref><ref name=Ramalingam2010>{{cite journal | last=Ramalingam | first=Sivaprakash | last2=Kandavelou | first2=Karthikeyan | last3=Rajenderan | first3=Raja | last4=Chandrasegaran | first4=Srinivasan | title=Creating Designed Zinc-Finger Nucleases with Minimal Cytotoxicity | journal=Journal of Molecular Biology | publisher=Elsevier BV | volume=405 | issue=3 | year=2011 | issn=0022-2836 | doi=10.1016/j.jmb.2010.10.043 | pages=630–641}}</ref>

